        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 5.  DONATIONS INTER VIVOS
SECTION 1.  GENERAL DISPOSITIONS
Art. 1526.  Onerous donation
The rules peculiar to donations inter vivos do not apply to a donation that is burdened with an obligation imposed on the donee that results in a material advantage to the donor, unless at the time of the donation the cost of performing the obligation is less than two-thirds of the value of the thing donated.</p>
        </content>
